[Amit Varma]: Pranay and Hamsini, welcome back to the scene and the unseen. So, help me make sense of

00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:20.920
[Amit Varma]: what's happening in these elections. You've had Nawaz Sharif sort of being defined against

00:27:20.920 --> 00:27:25.400
[Amit Varma]: a military jihadist complex, which is on the downswing both in terms of what the world

00:27:25.400 --> 00:27:31.040
[Amit Varma]: thinks of it and in terms of dealing with domestic matters. So, they've used the Supreme

00:27:31.040 --> 00:27:35.680
[Amit Varma]: Court as a puppet to get Nawaz out of the way. They've installed a puppet prime minister.

00:27:35.680 --> 00:27:39.680
[Amit Varma]: And now you have elections coming up. So, lay it out for me. What's at stake here? Who

00:27:39.680 --> 00:27:43.600
[Guest 1]: are the players in this game? And what's likely to happen?

00:27:43.600 --> 00:27:48.480
[Guest 1]: Before we get into these elections, I think it'll be good if Pranay, you told us how the

00:27:48.480 --> 00:27:53.120
[Guest 1]: National Assembly elections in Pakistan actually work, right? With respect to vote shares in

00:27:53.120 --> 00:27:55.240
[Guest 2]: provinces and so on.

00:27:55.240 --> 00:28:05.800
[Guest 2]: Yeah. So, think of it this way, that the electoral seats, basically Pakistan is dominated by

00:28:05.800 --> 00:28:13.360
[Guest 2]: one state. Okay. So, the total number of seats in the assembly are 342. Not all of them go

00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:18.800
[Guest 2]: for elections. They are sort of, some of them are reserved seats, etc.

00:28:18.800 --> 00:28:20.000
[Guest 1]: For minorities and women.

00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:25.800
[Guest 2]: Yeah, minorities and women. So, around 270 will go to vote in these elections. Now, the

00:28:25.800 --> 00:28:35.880
[Guest 2]: Punjab dominance is that nearly 170 seats out of 342 belong to Punjab. Okay. So, the

00:28:35.880 --> 00:28:42.000
[Guest 2]: second highest state, which is Sindh, it is less than half of that number. It has 75 seats.

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:49.560
[Guest 2]: So, anyone who controls Punjab sort of is the big person in town. In the last elections

00:28:49.560 --> 00:28:56.400
[Guest 2]: now, Nawaz Sharif's party really sweeped the entire Punjab. Okay. And they had close to

00:28:56.400 --> 00:29:04.880
[Guest 2]: 178 seats or something like that. So, because of that, they were the big party there. Now,

00:29:04.880 --> 00:29:11.400
[Guest 2]: what's happening now? Because PMLN has now lost favor of the Pakistani military jihadi

00:29:11.400 --> 00:29:15.800
[Guest 2]: complex, there are some other formations who are coming up. Now, there is something called

00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:22.520
[Guest 2]: the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf, which is led by Imran Khan and his election symbol obviously

00:29:22.520 --> 00:29:28.480
[Guest 2]: is a cricket bat. I don't know why not a ball, but it's a cricket bat. So, Imran Khan is

00:29:28.480 --> 00:29:34.360
[Guest 2]: the, his party actually rules this thing called the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, which is another state.

00:29:34.360 --> 00:29:40.120
[Guest 2]: That state just has now 50 seats totally. These are the two big formations. The third

00:29:40.120 --> 00:29:45.600
[Guest 2]: formation is the Pakistani People's Party, which is Benazir Bhutto's party. Now, it is

00:29:45.600 --> 00:29:52.520
[Guest 2]: being led by her son. Now, over the time, PPP's influence has waned. And even in these

00:29:52.520 --> 00:29:58.520
[Guest 2]: elections, it is only restricted to sins that they might perform well. These are the three

00:29:58.520 --> 00:30:04.400
[Guest 2]: big parties. Some other parties are now Pakistani military jihadi complex is also trying to

00:30:04.400 --> 00:30:09.960
[Guest 2]: mainstream militants. So, there is always like a palimpsest of militants who keep coming

00:30:09.960 --> 00:30:16.960
[Guest 2]: into the electoral setup. Earlier, you had some jihadi elements. Now, you have these

00:30:16.960 --> 00:30:23.800
[Guest 2]: guys Hafiz Saeed has a party called the Milli Muslim League that might contest. So, there

00:30:23.800 --> 00:30:27.800
[Guest 2]: are... And they are backed by the military jihadi complex. Yeah, it is a part of the

00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:31.880
[Guest 2]: military jihadi. They are the jihadi part of the military jihadi. So, it is very clear

00:30:31.880 --> 00:30:37.440
[Guest 2]: they are trying to mainstream it. There are militant Barelvi outfits also. There is a

00:30:37.440 --> 00:30:43.520
[Guest 2]: Pakistani Labaik party. And they are also trying. So, there are many, many layers of

00:30:43.520 --> 00:30:50.440
[Guest 2]: these militant guys who are also sort of contesting. So, these are the main guys in the elections.

00:30:50.440 --> 00:30:58.120
[Guest 2]: Now, Pakistani army has made its choice. It looks like Imran Khan is their man and a few

00:30:58.120 --> 00:31:03.480
[Guest 2]: reasons for that. First, they hated the PM and Nawaz Sharif. And even though Nawaz Sharif

00:31:03.480 --> 00:31:08.760
[Guest 2]: won't be contesting elections, they fear that his family will still be in control and he

00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:13.120
[Guest 2]: might again come back. So, they are trying to restrict them. They are doing that in a

00:31:13.120 --> 00:31:21.040
[Guest 2]: few ways. One, they are obviously helping Imran Khan project his party's name everywhere.

00:31:21.040 --> 00:31:26.680
[Guest 2]: Second, they have split the Pakistani Muslim League itself. And there was this Interior

00:31:26.680 --> 00:31:32.120
[Guest 2]: Minister Nisar Chaudhary who was from the Nawaz Sharif faction. Now, he split from the

00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:38.120
[Guest 2]: PMLN and he is contesting elections alone. And he was allotted the symbol of a jeep,

00:31:38.120 --> 00:31:43.560
[Guest 2]: which very obviously evokes images of the Pakistani military itself. And not only did

00:31:43.560 --> 00:31:50.440
[Guest 2]: that happen, a lot of people started quitting PMLN. And by some strange luck, a lot of these

00:31:50.440 --> 00:31:57.000
[Guest 2]: independents have been given the jeep symbol. So, this is like the jeep party. So, this

00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:02.160
[Guest 2]: is the jeep party, which is sort of, they don't call themselves a party, by the way.

00:32:02.160 --> 00:32:07.400
[Guest 2]: They are saying we are not a group, but we know what it is.

00:32:07.400 --> 00:32:14.720
[Guest 2]: What might happen is because PTI does not have a great presence in Punjab, these jeepers

00:32:14.720 --> 00:32:21.640
[Guest 2]: plus the PTI might collaborate and you might have a formation which can run.

00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:27.480
[Amit Varma]: And also Imran in the past has sort of shown his sympathy for militants anyway. Of course.

00:32:27.480 --> 00:32:32.400
[Amit Varma]: So he's always sort of been, you know, wanting to get into the good books of the military

00:32:32.400 --> 00:32:36.120
[Guest 2]: jihadi complex. Yeah, he is. I mean, the party was started

00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:42.920
[Guest 2]: by, now the interesting thing is even Nawaz Sharif's party was bankrolled by the Pakistani

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:47.960
[Guest 2]: army back in the 80s when Benazir Bhutto was just rising. This was late 80s.

00:32:47.960 --> 00:32:52.720
[Guest 2]: So as a counterpoint to that. So, there was this formation called the IJI,

00:32:52.720 --> 00:32:58.520
[Guest 2]: which was formed and Nawaz Sharif was a businessman who was brought in to do this. But over time,

00:32:58.520 --> 00:33:03.960
[Guest 2]: Nawaz Sharif now with, you know, 30 years of politics behind him wanted to do things

00:33:03.960 --> 00:33:08.320
[Guest 2]: his own way and that was too much for the Pakistani army.

00:33:08.320 --> 00:33:15.240
[Guest 2]: So now you have another case here and they are trying to form this party called the PTI.

00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:22.720
[Guest 2]: Obviously, they emerge, they come up every time the Pakistani army wants them to do,

00:33:22.720 --> 00:33:28.560
[Guest 2]: wants them to create all these noises. So yes, it looks like they are the Pakistani

00:33:28.560 --> 00:33:32.600
[Amit Varma]: army's guys. All very entertaining. So, is the army also

00:33:32.600 --> 00:33:36.400
[Amit Varma]: going to rig the elections in a manner of speaking? Because like there is an army person

00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:39.960
[Amit Varma]: at every booth, for example, they're pretty much controlling the physical logistics.

00:33:39.960 --> 00:33:45.160
[Guest 2]: Yeah. So that's, that's the interesting thing. And I don't know how that would work out.

00:33:45.160 --> 00:33:52.160
[Guest 2]: My guess is they have already rigged the election. You don't need to rig the ballot process to

00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:58.160
[Guest 2]: rig an election, right? You can rig it. They'll just put Nawaz Sharif behind bars, put his

00:33:58.160 --> 00:34:01.520
[Guest 2]: daughter behind bars. So, I mean, if that is not rigging, what is?

00:34:01.520 --> 00:34:08.480
[Guest 1]: You face so many insurmountable difficulties. And I think you wouldn't want to rig the election

00:34:08.480 --> 00:34:14.240
[Guest 1]: anymore because the army still wants that veneer of credibility, right? At some point,

00:34:14.240 --> 00:34:18.440
[Guest 1]: they still, they've always maintained the prop of a civilian government to show that

00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:24.720
[Guest 1]: there is some aspect of democracy within Pakistan. So if they go any further, then I think they

00:34:24.720 --> 00:34:28.160
[Guest 1]: will be tipping that balance and they won't want to do that necessarily because then they

00:34:28.160 --> 00:34:31.960
[Amit Varma]: can go back to military rule. But does that matter anymore? Because everyone

00:34:31.960 --> 00:34:35.320
[Amit Varma]: in the international community, for example, knows the real score anywhere, right?

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:40.760
[Guest 1]: No, I think it does matter because recently Pakistan has been put on the FATF, right?

00:34:40.760 --> 00:34:47.320
[Guest 2]: The Financial Action Task Force, for not cracking down on terrorism and money laundry and things

00:34:47.320 --> 00:34:51.440
[Amit Varma]: like that. And I don't know, what do you think, Pranay?

00:34:51.440 --> 00:34:58.240
[Guest 2]: I think the difference this time is because Nawaz Sharif is extremely popular still. And

00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:03.600
[Guest 2]: in fact, after what the army has done to him and put him behind jail, etc, there's a greater

00:35:03.600 --> 00:35:08.720
[Guest 2]: sympathy wave for him as well. So he's no walkover either. He's a seasoned politician.

00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:14.960
[Guest 2]: So if the Pakistan army goes overboard, there might be, you know, pushback from the supporters

00:35:14.960 --> 00:35:20.480
[Guest 2]: of Nawaz Sharif, which didn't exist earlier because, you know, there was only one game

00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:25.600
[Guest 2]: in town earlier. But now there is at least a hint of some political opposition.

00:35:25.600 --> 00:35:29.840
[Amit Varma]: Is there space for such a backlash to express itself? I mean, if it's basically an army

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:33.760
[Amit Varma]: run country, they can just clamp down on any dissent, right?

